{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1099,"text":"I study ants"},{"time":2718,"text":"in the desert, in the tropical forest"},{"time":6015,"text":"and in my kitchen,"},{"time":7543,"text":"and in the hills around Silicon Valley where I live."},{"time":11563,"text":"I've recently realized that ants"},{"time":13239,"text":"are using interactions differently"},{"time":15517,"text":"in different environments,"},{"time":17345,"text":"and that got me thinking\nthat we could learn from this"},{"time":19345,"text":"about other systems,"},{"time":20900,"text":"like brains and data networks that we engineer,"},{"time":26488,"text":"and even cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29334,"text":"So what all these systems have in common"},{"time":31086,"text":"is that there's no central control."},{"time":33943,"text":"An ant colony consists of sterile female workers --"},{"time":37763,"text":"those are the ants you see walking around â€”"},{"time":40149,"text":"and then one or more reproductive females"},{"time":42305,"text":"who just lay the eggs."},{"time":44408,"text":"They don't give any instructions."},{"time":46417,"text":"Even though they're called queens,"},{"time":48401,"text":"they don't tell anybody what to do."},{"time":50566,"text":"So in an ant colony, there's no one in charge,"},{"time":53842,"text":"and all systems like this without central control"},{"time":56620,"text":"are regulated using very simple interactions."},{"time":60549,"text":"Ants interact using smell."},{"time":63276,"text":"They smell with their antennae,"},{"time":65463,"text":"and they interact with their antennae,"},{"time":68224,"text":"so when one ant touches another with its antennae,"},{"time":71233,"text":"it can tell, for example, if the other ant"},{"time":72840,"text":"is a nestmate"},{"time":74474,"text":"and what task that other ant has been doing."},{"time":78710,"text":"So here you see a lot of ants moving around"},{"time":81910,"text":"and interacting in a lab arena"},{"time":83843,"text":"that's connected by tubes to two other arenas."},{"time":87281,"text":"So when one ant meets another,"},{"time":89785,"text":"it doesn't matter which ant it meets,"},{"time":91874,"text":"and they're actually not transmitting"},{"time":93759,"text":"any kind of complicated signal or message."},{"time":97224,"text":"All that matters to the ant is the rate"},{"time":99335,"text":"at which it meets other ants."},{"time":102156,"text":"And all of these interactions, taken together,"},{"time":104913,"text":"produce a network."},{"time":107418,"text":"So this is the network of the ants"},{"time":109628,"text":"that you just saw moving around in the arena,"},{"time":112272,"text":"and it's this constantly shifting network"},{"time":115559,"text":"that produces the behavior of the colony,"},{"time":118079,"text":"like whether all the ants are hiding inside the nest,"},{"time":120960,"text":"or how many are going out to forage."},{"time":123654,"text":"A brain actually works in the same way,"},{"time":125413,"text":"but what's great about ants is"},{"time":126913,"text":"that you can see the whole network as it happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131780,"text":"There are more than 12,000 species of ants,"},{"time":134880,"text":"in every conceivable environment,"},{"time":137005,"text":"and they're using interactions differently"},{"time":139654,"text":"to meet different environmental challenges."},{"time":142422,"text":"So one important environmental challenge"},{"time":144727,"text":"that every system has to deal with"},{"time":146597,"text":"is operating costs, just what it takes"},{"time":148680,"text":"to run the system."},{"time":150945,"text":"And another environmental challenge is resources,"},{"time":153493,"text":"finding them and collecting them."},{"time":155829,"text":"In the desert, operating costs are high"},{"time":158612,"text":"because water is scarce,"},{"time":160385,"text":"and the seed-eating ants that I study in the desert"},{"time":162884,"text":"have to spend water to get water."},{"time":165784,"text":"So an ant outside foraging,"},{"time":167923,"text":"searching for seeds in the hot sun,"},{"time":169960,"text":"just loses water into the air."},{"time":171967,"text":"But the colony gets its water"},{"time":173631,"text":"by metabolizing the fats out of the seeds"},{"time":175397,"text":"that they eat."},{"time":177331,"text":"So in this environment, interactions are used"},{"time":180490,"text":"to activate foraging."},{"time":182039,"text":"An outgoing forager doesn't go out unless"},{"time":184303,"text":"it gets enough interactions with returning foragers,"},{"time":186876,"text":"and what you see are the returning foragers"},{"time":188866,"text":"going into the tunnel, into the nest,"},{"time":190690,"text":"and meeting outgoing foragers on their way out."},{"time":193326,"text":"This makes sense for the ant colony,"},{"time":194949,"text":"because the more food there is out there,"},{"time":197272,"text":"the more quickly the foragers find it,"},{"time":199123,"text":"the faster they come back,"},{"time":200359,"text":"and the more foragers they send out."},{"time":203160,"text":"The system works to stay stopped,"},{"time":205667,"text":"unless something positive happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207682,"text":"So interactions function to activate foragers."},{"time":211563,"text":"And we've been studying\nthe evolution of this system."},{"time":214470,"text":"First of all, there's variation."},{"time":215561,"text":"It turns out that colonies are different."},{"time":218040,"text":"On dry days, some colonies forage less,"},{"time":220736,"text":"so colonies are different in how"},{"time":222241,"text":"they manage this trade-off"},{"time":223595,"text":"between spending water to search for seeds"},{"time":226763,"text":"and getting water back in the form of seeds."},{"time":230083,"text":"And we're trying to understand why"},{"time":231802,"text":"some colonies forage less than others"},{"time":233942,"text":"by thinking about ants as neurons,"},{"time":236267,"text":"using models from neuroscience."},{"time":238605,"text":"So just as a neuron adds up its stimulation"},{"time":241279,"text":"from other neurons to decide whether to fire,"},{"time":243285,"text":"an ant adds up its stimulation from other ants"},{"time":246170,"text":"to decide whether to forage."},{"time":248193,"text":"And what we're looking for is whether there might be"},{"time":249830,"text":"small differences among colonies"},{"time":251822,"text":"in how many interactions each ant needs"},{"time":255136,"text":"before it's willing to go out and forage,"},{"time":257062,"text":"because a colony like that would forage less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260829,"text":"And this raises an analogous question about brains."},{"time":263968,"text":"We talk about the brain,"},{"time":265380,"text":"but of course every brain is slightly different,"},{"time":268270,"text":"and maybe there are some individuals"},{"time":269649,"text":"or some conditions"},{"time":270968,"text":"in which the electrical properties of neurons are such"},{"time":274190,"text":"that they require more stimulus to fire,"},{"time":278060,"text":"and that would lead to differences in brain function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281786,"text":"So in order to ask evolutionary questions,"},{"time":284120,"text":"we need to know about reproductive success."},{"time":286799,"text":"This is a map of the study site"},{"time":289124,"text":"where I have been tracking this population"},{"time":291677,"text":"of harvester ant colonies for 28 years,"},{"time":294970,"text":"which is about as long as a colony lives."},{"time":297232,"text":"Each symbol is a colony,"},{"time":299331,"text":"and the size of the symbol is\nhow many offspring it had,"},{"time":302597,"text":"because we were able to use genetic variation"},{"time":304510,"text":"to match up parent and offspring colonies,"},{"time":307221,"text":"that is, to figure out which colonies"},{"time":310518,"text":"were founded by a daughter queen"},{"time":312443,"text":"produced by which parent colony."},{"time":314511,"text":"And this was amazing for me, after all these years,"},{"time":316513,"text":"to find out, for example, that colony 154,"},{"time":319641,"text":"whom I've known well for many years,"},{"time":321817,"text":"is a great-grandmother."},{"time":323636,"text":"Here's her daughter colony,"},{"time":325376,"text":"here's her granddaughter colony,"},{"time":328060,"text":"and these are her great-granddaughter colonies."},{"time":330452,"text":"And by doing this, I was able to learn"},{"time":332477,"text":"that offspring colonies resemble parent colonies"},{"time":335760,"text":"in their decisions about which days are so hot"},{"time":337977,"text":"that they don't forage,"},{"time":339755,"text":"and the offspring of parent colonies"},{"time":341219,"text":"live so far from each other that the ants never meet,"},{"time":344125,"text":"so the ants of the offspring colony"},{"time":346414,"text":"can't be learning this from the parent colony."},{"time":348658,"text":"And so our next step is to look"},{"time":350039,"text":"for the genetic variation\nunderlying this resemblance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355315,"text":"So then I was able to ask, okay, who's doing better?"},{"time":359440,"text":"Over the time of the study,"},{"time":360900,"text":"and especially in the past 10 years,"},{"time":362365,"text":"there's been a very severe and deepening drought"},{"time":365673,"text":"in the Southwestern U.S.,"},{"time":367800,"text":"and it turns out that the\ncolonies that conserve water,"},{"time":370853,"text":"that stay in when it's really hot outside,"},{"time":375282,"text":"and thus sacrifice getting as much food as possible,"},{"time":377914,"text":"are the ones more likely to have offspring colonies."},{"time":380859,"text":"So all this time, I thought that colony 154"},{"time":383128,"text":"was a loser, because on really dry days,"},{"time":385798,"text":"there'd be just this trickle of foraging,"},{"time":387666,"text":"while the other colonies were out"},{"time":389257,"text":"foraging, getting lots of food,"},{"time":391374,"text":"but in fact, colony 154 is a huge success."},{"time":394394,"text":"She's a matriarch."},{"time":395726,"text":"She's one of the rare great-grandmothers on the site."},{"time":398778,"text":"To my knowledge, this is the first time"},{"time":401563,"text":"that we've been able to track"},{"time":403202,"text":"the ongoing evolution of collective behavior"},{"time":406203,"text":"in a natural population of animals"},{"time":408320,"text":"and find out what's actually working best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412977,"text":"Now, the Internet uses an algorithm"},{"time":415398,"text":"to regulate the flow of data"},{"time":418251,"text":"that's very similar to the one"},{"time":420478,"text":"that the harvester ants are using to regulate"},{"time":422854,"text":"the flow of foragers."},{"time":424395,"text":"And guess what we call this analogy?"},{"time":427761,"text":"The anternet is coming."},{"time":429279,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":431000,"text":"So data doesn't leave the source computer"},{"time":434454,"text":"unless it gets a signal that there's enough bandwidth"},{"time":437315,"text":"for it to travel on."},{"time":440044,"text":"In the early days of the Internet,"},{"time":441485,"text":"when operating costs were really high"},{"time":443759,"text":"and it was really important not to lose any data,"},{"time":446986,"text":"then the system was set up for interactions"},{"time":449143,"text":"to activate the flow of data."},{"time":452205,"text":"It's interesting that the ants are using an algorithm"},{"time":454590,"text":"that's so similar to the one that we recently invented,"},{"time":458486,"text":"but this is only one of a handful of ant algorithms"},{"time":461439,"text":"that we know about,"},{"time":462858,"text":"and ants have had 130 million years"},{"time":466051,"text":"to evolve a lot of good ones,"},{"time":468077,"text":"and I think it's very likely"},{"time":469583,"text":"that some of the other 12,000 species"},{"time":472140,"text":"are going to have interesting algorithms"},{"time":474837,"text":"for data networks"},{"time":475861,"text":"that we haven't even thought of yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478558,"text":"So what happens when operating costs are low?"},{"time":481643,"text":"Operating costs are low in the tropics,"},{"time":483430,"text":"because it's very humid, and it's easy for the ants"},{"time":485526,"text":"to be outside walking around."},{"time":488350,"text":"But the ants are so abundant"},{"time":490003,"text":"and diverse in the tropics"},{"time":491821,"text":"that there's a lot of competition."},{"time":494419,"text":"Whatever resource one species is using,"},{"time":496371,"text":"another species is likely to be using that"},{"time":499543,"text":"at the same time."},{"time":501922,"text":"So in this environment, interactions are used"},{"time":504530,"text":"in the opposite way."},{"time":506475,"text":"The system keeps going"},{"time":507870,"text":"unless something negative happens,"},{"time":509424,"text":"and one species that I study makes circuits"},{"time":511591,"text":"in the trees of foraging ants"},{"time":513750,"text":"going from the nest to a food source and back,"},{"time":516731,"text":"just round and round,"},{"time":518060,"text":"unless something negative happens,"},{"time":519502,"text":"like an interaction"},{"time":521111,"text":"with ants of another species."},{"time":523850,"text":"So here's an example of ant security."},{"time":526787,"text":"In the middle, there's an ant"},{"time":528645,"text":"plugging the nest entrance with its head"},{"time":531108,"text":"in response to interactions with another species."},{"time":534101,"text":"Those are the little ones running around"},{"time":535760,"text":"with their abdomens up in the air."},{"time":538511,"text":"But as soon as the threat is passed,"},{"time":540557,"text":"the entrance is open again,"},{"time":543312,"text":"and maybe there are situations"},{"time":545102,"text":"in computer security"},{"time":546191,"text":"where operating costs are low enough"},{"time":548397,"text":"that we could just block access temporarily"},{"time":551772,"text":"in response to an immediate threat,"},{"time":553965,"text":"and then open it again,"},{"time":555991,"text":"instead of trying to build"},{"time":557260,"text":"a permanent firewall or fortress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561240,"text":"So another environmental challenge"},{"time":563180,"text":"that all systems have to deal with"},{"time":564875,"text":"is resources, finding and collecting them."},{"time":570327,"text":"And to do this, ants solve the problem"},{"time":572000,"text":"of collective search,"},{"time":573258,"text":"and this is a problem that's of great interest"},{"time":574834,"text":"right now in robotics,"},{"time":576318,"text":"because we've understood that,"},{"time":578050,"text":"rather than sending a single,"},{"time":579664,"text":"sophisticated, expensive robot out"},{"time":583159,"text":"to explore another planet"},{"time":584576,"text":"or to search a burning building,"},{"time":587143,"text":"that instead, it may be more effective"},{"time":589743,"text":"to get a group of cheaper robots"},{"time":594120,"text":"exchanging only minimal information,"},{"time":596665,"text":"and that's the way that ants do it."},{"time":599464,"text":"So the invasive Argentine ant"},{"time":601229,"text":"makes expandable search networks."},{"time":603559,"text":"They're good at dealing with the main problem"},{"time":605832,"text":"of collective search,"},{"time":607163,"text":"which is the trade-off between"},{"time":609729,"text":"searching very thoroughly"},{"time":611065,"text":"and covering a lot of ground."},{"time":613062,"text":"And what they do is,"},{"time":613957,"text":"when there are many ants in a small space,"},{"time":616344,"text":"then each one can search very thoroughly"},{"time":618557,"text":"because there will be another ant nearby"},{"time":620181,"text":"searching over there,"},{"time":621538,"text":"but when there are a few ants"},{"time":623185,"text":"in a large space,"},{"time":625240,"text":"then they need to stretch out their paths"},{"time":627654,"text":"to cover more ground."},{"time":629457,"text":"I think they use interactions to assess density,"},{"time":632411,"text":"so when they're really crowded,"},{"time":633640,"text":"they meet more often,"},{"time":634742,"text":"and they search more thoroughly."},{"time":637207,"text":"Different ant species must use different algorithms,"},{"time":640607,"text":"because they've evolved to deal with"},{"time":643129,"text":"different resources,"},{"time":644800,"text":"and it could be really useful to know about this,"},{"time":647359,"text":"and so we recently asked ants"},{"time":649001,"text":"to solve the collective search problem"},{"time":651451,"text":"in the extreme environment"},{"time":652819,"text":"of microgravity"},{"time":654377,"text":"in the International Space Station."},{"time":656353,"text":"When I first saw this picture, I thought,"},{"time":657898,"text":"Oh no, they've mounted the habitat vertically,"},{"time":660755,"text":"but then I realized that, of course, it doesn't matter."},{"time":663373,"text":"So the idea here is that the ants"},{"time":666010,"text":"are working so hard to hang on"},{"time":667980,"text":"to the wall or the floor or whatever you call it"},{"time":671037,"text":"that they're less likely to interact,"},{"time":674046,"text":"and so the relationship between"},{"time":675290,"text":"how crowded they are and how often they meet"},{"time":677410,"text":"would be messed up."},{"time":679135,"text":"We're still analyzing the data."},{"time":680530,"text":"I don't have the results yet."},{"time":682494,"text":"But it would be interesting to know"},{"time":684188,"text":"how other species solve this problem"},{"time":686647,"text":"in different environments on Earth,"},{"time":689211,"text":"and so we're setting up a program"},{"time":690477,"text":"to encourage kids around the world"},{"time":692637,"text":"to try this experiment with different species."},{"time":695173,"text":"It's very simple."},{"time":696940,"text":"It can be done with cheap materials."},{"time":699030,"text":"And that way, we could make a global map"},{"time":701863,"text":"of ant collective search algorithms."},{"time":705210,"text":"And I think it's pretty likely that the invasive species,"},{"time":707693,"text":"the ones that come into our buildings,"},{"time":709842,"text":"are going to be really good at this,"},{"time":711584,"text":"because they're in your kitchen"},{"time":713432,"text":"because they're really good\nat finding food and water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717339,"text":"So the most familiar resource for ants"},{"time":720604,"text":"is a picnic,"},{"time":721919,"text":"and this is a clustered resource."},{"time":724064,"text":"When there's one piece of fruit,"},{"time":725063,"text":"there's likely to be another piece of fruit nearby,"},{"time":727578,"text":"and the ants that specialize on clustered resources"},{"time":731010,"text":"use interactions for recruitment."},{"time":732952,"text":"So when one ant meets another,"},{"time":734229,"text":"or when it meets a chemical deposited"},{"time":735854,"text":"on the ground by another,"},{"time":737590,"text":"then it changes direction to follow"},{"time":739423,"text":"in the direction of the interaction,"},{"time":740996,"text":"and that's how you get the trail of ants"},{"time":742973,"text":"sharing your picnic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744386,"text":"Now this is a place where I think we might be able"},{"time":746081,"text":"to learn something from ants about cancer."},{"time":749822,"text":"I mean, first, it's obvious that we could do a lot"},{"time":751803,"text":"to prevent cancer"},{"time":753413,"text":"by not allowing people to spread around"},{"time":755990,"text":"or sell the toxins that promote"},{"time":757934,"text":"the evolution of cancer in our bodies,"},{"time":760714,"text":"but I don't think the ants can help us much with this"},{"time":763060,"text":"because ants never poison their own colonies."},{"time":766418,"text":"But we might be able to learn something from ants"},{"time":767750,"text":"about treating cancer."},{"time":769513,"text":"There are many different kinds of cancer."},{"time":771738,"text":"Each one originates in a particular part of the body,"},{"time":774716,"text":"and then some kinds of cancer will spread"},{"time":777682,"text":"or metastasize to particular other tissues"},{"time":780512,"text":"where they must be getting\nresources that they need."},{"time":783392,"text":"So if you think from the perspective"},{"time":785200,"text":"of early metastatic cancer cells"},{"time":787150,"text":"as they're out searching around"},{"time":788773,"text":"for the resources that they need,"},{"time":791090,"text":"if those resources are clustered,"},{"time":793073,"text":"they're likely to use interactions for recruitment,"},{"time":796086,"text":"and if we can figure out how\ncancer cells are recruiting,"},{"time":799179,"text":"then maybe we could set traps"},{"time":801526,"text":"to catch them before they become established."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805575,"text":"So ants are using interactions in different ways"},{"time":808810,"text":"in a huge variety of environments,"},{"time":811412,"text":"and we could learn from this"},{"time":813233,"text":"about other systems that operate"},{"time":815010,"text":"without central control."},{"time":817347,"text":"Using only simple interactions,"},{"time":819326,"text":"ant colonies have been performing"},{"time":821121,"text":"amazing feats for more than 130 million years."},{"time":824754,"text":"We have a lot to learn from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826894,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829632,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}